The following theorem is the main theorem in this section.
Theorem 3.18. Let T be the companion matrix of the n-degree primitive
polynomial f(x) = xn+cn‚àí1xn‚àí1+cn‚àí2xn‚àí2+ ¬∑ ¬∑ ¬∑+c1x+1. Let cj = 1 for some
j (1 < j < n). And let T k + cj+1T k+1 + ¬∑ ¬∑ ¬∑+ cn‚àí1T k+(n‚àíj‚àí1) + T k+(n‚àíj) = I.
Then ps(n‚àí j + 1) = k.
