4 Algorithms to compute Phase shifts
Using the theorems outlined above, we give an algorithm to find the phase shifts
of the sequences generated by companion matrices of primitive polynomials.
Algorithm FindPhaseShiftsOfLFSM
Input: n, The 1st column (cn‚àí1, cn‚àí2, ¬∑ ¬∑ ¬∑ , c1, 1) of the companion matrix T of
an n-degree primitive polynomial f(x) = xn+cn‚àí1xn‚àí1+cn‚àí2xn‚àí2+¬∑ ¬∑ ¬∑+c1x+1.
Output: The phase shifts ps(i)(1 ‚â§ i ‚â§ n) of the ith column of S.
BEGIN
ps(1)‚Üê 2n ‚àí 1
ps(n)‚Üê 1
count ‚Üê 0
Step 1. Find m = min{j|cj = 1, 1 ‚â§ j < n};
Step 2. for h‚Üê 1 to m‚àí 1
do {
ps(n‚àí h)‚Üê h+ 1
count ‚Üê count + 1
}
if count > n‚àí 3 then Stop.
Step 3. ps(n‚àím)‚Üê k subject to T k + T k‚àím = I
count ‚Üê count + 1
if count > n‚àí 3 then Stop.
Step 4. Find M = max{j|cj = 1,m ‚â§ j ‚â§ n‚àí 1 };
Step 5. for l‚Üê n‚àí 1 downto M + 1
do {
ps(n‚àí l + 1)‚Üê ps(n‚àí l)‚àí 1
