Then, the exponent is obtained in the following way:
1. Count the number of positions from the beginning of the string until the dot
character ‚Äù  ‚Äù is found with the function c : dom (ŒΩsd)‚Üí dom (ŒΩN). This will
provide the initial exponent.
2. Remove the dot character ‚Äù  ‚Äù from the string and then remove the 0s at
the beginning of it. At the same time, while removing the 0s, successively
decrement the exponent by applying the function a : Œ£‚àó√ódom (ŒΩN)‚Üí Œ£‚àó√ó
dom (ŒΩZ). The mantissa and the exponent at the output are the remaining
chunk of the string and the decremented exponent, respectively.
3. Apply the wrapping function in order to wrap the exponent the fixed man-
tissa and the periodic mantissa:
Œπw(e) := u = ##e0#e1#...#ek##,
Œπw(mf ) := v = ##mf,0#mf,1#...#mf,k##,
Œπw(mp) := w = ##mp,0#mp,1#...#mp,k##,
and then concatenate u and v such as w = uv ‚àà dom (ŒΩnsd) .
