3.1 Strong Bisimulation for Many-Valued Modal Languages
The following definition captures the idea of moving ‚Äòback and forth‚Äô between
two H-models by matching steps (‚Äòmodulo‚Äô t) in both directions.
Definition 4 (t-bisimulations). Given two H-models M = „ÄàS, g, v„Äâ and
M‚Ä≤ = „ÄàS‚Ä≤, g‚Ä≤, v‚Ä≤„Äâ and a truth value t ‚àà H (t 6= ‚ä•), a non-empty relation
Z ‚äÜ S√óS‚Ä≤ is a t-bisimulation between M and M‚Ä≤ if for any pair „Äàs, s‚Ä≤„Äâ ‚àà Z
