Two states s and s‚Ä≤ are called t-bisimilar (notation s ‚Üît s‚Ä≤ or M, s ‚Üît M‚Ä≤, s‚Ä≤)
if there is a t-bisimulation Z between M and M‚Ä≤ such that sZs‚Ä≤.
We can now prove the basic theorem which states that t-bisimulation implies
