Lemma 2 (Yokouchi‚Äôs Lemma [18]). Let R and S be two relations defined
on the same set T , R being confluent and noetherian, and S having the diamond
property. Suppose moreover that the diagram D as shown in the Figure 1(b)
holds: Then the relation R‚àó ‚ó¶ S ‚ó¶R‚àó has the diamond property.
proof (Sketch). The proof starts by generalizing the diagram D of the lemma
as the diagram D‚Ä≤ in the Figure 1(c). This generalization is proved by noetherian
induction using the predicate
P (x) := ‚àÄy, z. xR‚àóz ‚àß xSy ‚áí ‚àÉu.(yR‚àóu ‚àß zR‚àó ‚ó¶ S ‚ó¶R‚àóu)
