The following lemma plays a key role of the proof of Picard‚Äôs little theorem.
Lemma 1 (lifting). The following assertions are equivalent over RCA0.
1. WKL0.
2. Let D0, D ‚äÜ C be open sets, and let (X,D, pi, Uij , Vi, piij) be a covering space
of D. If D0 is simply connected and f is a continuous function from D0
to D, then, there exists a continuous function fÀÜ from D0 to X such that
pi ‚ó¶ fÀÜ = f .
Proof. We first show 1 ‚Üí 2 in case D0 = [0, 1]. We reason within WKL0. Let
D0 = [0, 1] and aij = j/2i+1 for all j ‚â§ 2i+1. By WKL0, we can define Wi as
follows:
Wi =
