(R) F (y,x) = G(sup{F (z,x) | z < y}, y,x)
We write PrimS instead of PrimS(‚àÖ).
If B is a set and X is the unary function X(x) = x ‚à© B then we may write
PrimS(B) for PrimS(X).
If B ‚äÜ Œ± and Œ± is an ordinal that is closed under PrimO(B) functions then
we call a function f : Œ±n ‚àí‚Üí Œ± PrimS(B) iff it is the restriction of a PrimS(B)
function.
An n-ary relation R ‚äÜ V n is PrimS(X) if there is a PrimS(X) function
FR : V n ‚àí‚Üí V s.t. FR(x) = 0 iff x ‚àà R.
Theorem 1. If Œ± is closed under PrimO functions, then every PrimO(B) func-
