4 Applications
The following theorems are similar to Theorem 7 and 9 in [6] which provide a
connection between Œ±-recursion theory and ordinal computability. The proofs
found in [6] explicitely give a truth function for bounded formulas in LŒ± which
is Œ±-computable if Œ± is sufficiently closed with respect to ordinal arithmetic.
Instead we use facts from the classical theory of PrimS functions to obtain these
results.
Theorem 2. If Œ± is an ordinal closed under PrimO functions then A ‚äÜ Œ± is
