Abstract. Previously ‚Äî in CiE 2005 [2005] ‚Äî we have given an order-
ing of finite trees and showed that it is a well ordering reaching up to
the small Veblen ordinal. Here we extend this ordering to finite labeled
trees ‚Äî similar to Takeutis ordinal diagrams [1975] ‚Äî and show that
this extended ordering is also a well ordering.
Key words: ordinals, ordinal notation, finite labeled trees
1
We have given a wellordered set of labels Œõ and consider finite trees with labels
at the nodes. In the trees the branches are ordered ‚Äî from left to right. Below
there are four examples of finite labeled trees
