Corollary 1 For all n ‚â• 1 Dapm contains a continuum of initial segments each
of which is isomorphic to Boolean algebra of subsets of a n-element set.
In conclusion we would like to announce another weak pm-reducibility:
A ‚â§wpm B ‚áê‚áí (‚àÉk)(‚àÉœà1, . . . , œàk)[A = œà‚àí11 (B) ‚à™ . . . ‚à™ œà‚àí1k (B)].
In this case we will talk that A is wpm-reducible to B via (œà1, . . . , œàk).
It is clear that ‚â§wpm is reflexive and transitive, hence it is a reducibility in
ordinary sense. It is also clear that A ‚â§apm B ‚áí A ‚â§wpm B and A ‚â§wpm B ‚áí
A ‚â§e B (moreover A ‚â§wpm B ‚áí A ‚â§s B) for all A and B, i.e. apm-reducibility
is a reducibility of enumeration type. We are able to construct two sets A and
B such that A 6‚â§apm B ‚àßA ‚â§wpm B.
We invite to study this wpm-reducibility as a reducibility of enumeration
type which has a good intuitive background.
