it; in other words, ‚àÉSWinP1(S, C
‚Ä≤‚Ä≤) ‚à® ‚àÉSWinP2(S, C
‚Ä≤‚Ä≤) (we used the fact here
that ‚àÉx(Œ± ‚à® Œ≤) is equivalent to ‚àÉxŒ± ‚à® ‚àÉxŒ≤). If no matter what first move P1
makes (to obtain C ‚Ä≤‚Ä≤) it is always the case that ‚àÉSWinP2(S, C
‚Ä≤‚Ä≤), then we can
