Definition 2.5. For any function f , we let PKf denote the class of all sets of
reals that are decidable by a time f machine. For any ordinal Œæ, we let PKŒæ
denote the class of all sets of reals that are decidable by a time Œ∑ machine for
some Œ∑ < Œæ.2 Likewise, we use the similar notations PHKf and P
