‚àÄx, y ‚àà U f(y)‚àí f(x) = (y ‚àí x)(f ‚Ä≤(x) + ef (x, y)).
We call this ef a differentiable condition function for f .
Proof. See [3].
Note that we can effectively find a differentiable condition function for a C1-
function.
