The first theorem is concerned with the uniform convergence of Fourier series.
Theorem 7. The following assertions are equivalent over RCA0.
1. WKL0.
2. If f ‚àà P2pi is a C1-function, then there exist real sequences {ak}k‚ààN and
{bk}k‚ààN such that Sn[{ak}{bk}] uniformly converges to f .
Proof. By Theorem 2 and Lemma 4, 1 ‚Üí 2 holds. For the converse, we assume
2. By Lemma 1, we only need to show that every periodic C1-function (with
period 2pi) is uniformly continuous. Let f ‚àà P2pi be a C1-function. Then, there
exist {ak}k‚ààN and {bk}k‚ààN such that Sn[{ak}{bk}] uniformly converges to f .
Since sinx and cosx are uniformly continuous, we can easily show that f is also
uniformly continuous. This completes the proof.
