Now we will describe notations used in our procedures.
Let Vu(E¬Ø) (Vm(E¬Ø)) denote the set of unmarked (marked) vertices which would be
removed from V (G‚Ä≤) if the edges E¬Ø were added to IM(G). The process of adding
edges to IM(G) is realized by the procedure ADD(E¬Ø) which adds the edges E¬Ø to
IM(G) and removes appropriate vertices and edges from G‚Ä≤ . Moreover, if |Vu(E¬Ø)| +
2|Vm(E¬Ø)| = 6|E¬Ø| + x and x > 0 then the procedure ADD(E¬Ø) marks x vertices which
are still in V (G‚Ä≤). The only exception is the situation when the last tree is processed. In
490 GrazÀôyna Zwoz¬¥niak
this case we have x = 0, but there are some cases when the number of removed vertices
may be larger than 6|E¬Ø|. That is why the size of IM(G) is n/6 +O(1).
