„ÄàA, (A0, 0A), ¬∑„Äâ with a disjunction of A into two subsets A0‚à™ 0A = A, A0‚à© 0A = ‚àÖ
and commutative partial operation ‚Äú¬∑‚Äù which satisfy the following properties:
(1) a¬∑b is defined iff a6=b and a, b ‚àà A0 (or a, b ‚àà 0A) with the product a¬∑b ‚àà 0A
(a¬∑b ‚àà A0 respectively);
(2) for all a, b, c ‚àà A if a¬∑b, a¬∑c, (a¬∑b)¬∑(a¬∑c) are defined, then (a¬∑b)¬∑(a¬∑c) = a;
(3) there exist distinct a, b, c, d ‚àà A such that products a¬∑b, b¬∑c, c¬∑d, d¬∑a are
defined and pairwise distinct.
Any free projective plane is freely generated by the set of ‚Äúpoints‚Äù {b1, b2} ‚à™
